Temporary Staffing Platform - INSTALL

Overview
This project has:
- a frontend in frontend/ built with React and Vite
- a backend in backend/ built with Node.js, Express, Prisma, and SQLite

Package requirements
Install:
- Node.js 20 or newer
- npm

Local backend setup
1. cd backend
2. npm install
3. npx prisma generate
4. npx prisma db push
5. npm run seed
6. node src/server.js 3000

Seeded admin account
- email: admin1@csc309.utoronto.ca
- password: 123123

Local frontend setup
1. cd frontend
2. npm install
3. create a file named .env.local with:
   VITE_BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:3000
4. npm run dev

Deployed services
- frontend: https://csc-309-a3-staffing-platform.vercel.app/
- backend: https://csc309-a3-staffing-platform.onrender.com

Deployment configuration

Backend on Render
- Root Directory: backend
- Build Command:
  npm install && npx prisma generate && npx prisma db push && npm run seed
- Start Command:
  node src/server.js $PORT
- Environment Variable:
  FRONTEND_ORIGIN=https://csc-309-a3-staffing-platform.vercel.app/

Frontend on Vercel
- Root Directory: frontend
- Framework Preset: Vite
- Environment Variable:
  VITE_BACKEND_URL=https://csc309-a3-staffing-platform.onrender.com

Notes
- The backend stores data in SQLite.
- The backend stores uploaded files locally in uploads/.
- On free hosting, SQLite data and uploaded files may be lost after redeploys or service resets.
- The backend health endpoint is:
  https://csc309-a3-staffing-platform.onrender.com/health
